H0.text: Cytoskeleton gives the cell an internal structure, analogous to the frame of a house.

H1.text: Cytoplasm is what gives the cell an internal structure, similar to the frame of a house.

H2.text: Cellulose gives the cell an internal structure, similar to how a houseâ€™s frame provides support.

H3.text: The endoskeleton gives the cell an internal structure, like the frame of a house.

A4.text: Its primary function is to give the cell its shape and mechanical resistance to deformation, and through association with extracellular connective tissue and other cells it stabilizes entire tissues.

A5.text: The cytoskeleton is a complex, dynamic network of interlinking protein filaments present in the cytoplasm of all cells, including those of bacteria and archaea.
